requestBody.description:
A device telemetry data.

The timestamp specifies the time in milliseconds at which the device telemetry measurements were taken.
This must be within 10 seconds of the timestamp returned by the `/v2/timestamp` endpoint.

Example of a GSM telemetry
---

```
[{
    "scan": {
        "gsm": [{
            "mcc": 262,
            "mnc": 1,
            "lac": 5126,
            "cid": 16504,
            "nmr": [
                { "bsic": "6", "bcch": "82" },
                { "bsic": "7", "bcch": "85" },
                { "bsic": "12", "bcch": "93" },
                { "bsic": "13", "bcch": "88" },
                { "bsic": "19", "bcch": "88" }
            ]
        }]
    },
    "payload": {
        "sensor": "data"
    },
    "timestamp": 1515169948976
}]
```

Example of a WLAN telemetry
---

```
[{
    "scan": {
        "wlan": [
            { "mac": "1c:1d:86:07:01:0f", "powrx": -45 },
            { "mac": "e4:f4:c6:d9:85:59", "powrx": -39 },
            { "mac": "1c:1d:86:07:01:0d", "powrx": -43 },
            { "mac": "1c:1d:86:07:01:0b", "powrx": -44 },
            { "mac": "1c:1d:86:07:01:04", "powrx": -58 },
            { "mac": "1c:1d:86:07:01:03", "powrx": -59 }
        ]
    },
    "payload": {
        "sensor": "data"
    },
    "timestamp": 1515169948976
}]
```

